{"id":482336,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I%27m_Going_Slightly_Mad","text":"I'm Going Slightly Mad is the second single from Queen's album Innuendo. The album was released on 4 March 1991. The song 'I'm Going Slightly Mad' was written by Freddie Mercury.\nVideo.\nThe video is shot in black and white and features the band dressed and acting in a ridiculous way. Brian May is dressed as a penguin. Roger Taylor wears a teapot on his head and rides a tricycle while Freddie Mercury is chasing him. Freddie Mercury wears a bunch of bananas as a wig. John Deacon is a jester.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Single_(music)","surface_form":"single","offset":37},{"uri":"Queen","surface_form":"Queen","offset":49},{"uri":"Album","surface_form":"album","offset":57},{"uri":"Innuendo_(album)","surface_form":"Innuendo","offset":63},{"uri":"Song","surface_form":"song","offset":117},{"uri":"Freddie_Mercury","surface_form":"Freddie Mercury","offset":162},{"uri":"Monochrome","surface_form":"black and white","offset":207},{"uri":"Band","surface_form":"band","offset":240},{"uri":"Dressed","surface_form":"dressed","offset":245},{"uri":"Acting","surface_form":"acting","offset":257},{"uri":"Ridiculous","surface_form":"ridiculous","offset":269},{"uri":"Brian_May","surface_form":"Brian May","offset":285},{"uri":"Penguin","surface_form":"penguin","offset":311},{"uri":"Roger_Taylor","surface_form":"Roger Taylor","offset":320},{"uri":"Teapot","surface_form":"teapot","offset":341},{"uri":"Head","surface_form":"head","offset":355},{"uri":"Tricycle","surface_form":"tricycle","offset":372},{"uri":"Banana","surface_form":"banana","offset":452},{"uri":"Wig","surface_form":"wig","offset":465},{"uri":"John_Deacon","surface_form":"John Deacon","offset":470}]}